&lt;li&gt;Jira Query Language (JQL) for searching, reporting, and automation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to troubleshoot and resolve technical issues independently while documenting solutions and assisting customers in configuring their Atlassian environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working remotely in a globally distributed team, demonstrating strong time management and self-motivation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus &lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Points&lt;/span&gt; For:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical knowledge beyond standard Atlassian administration, including:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of HTTP requests and how they work in APIs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with JSON data structures for integrations and configurations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic networking knowledge, including how network routing works.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of email protocols (SMTP, IMAP, POP) and how they interact with Jira Service Management notifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in scripting or automation, using languages such as: Python, Groovy, JavaScript or Bash.&lt;/li&gt;
